# Deploy and Git — User Must Ask First

Do **not** deploy to QNAP or push to GitHub unless the user **explicitly** requests it in the current message (e.g. “deploy to QNAP”, “push to git”, “commit and push”).

## QNAP deploy (off by default)

- Do not rsync/scp to `192.168.10.11`, rebuild Docker images, or `docker compose up` on the NAS after routine code changes.
- Local edits and local `npm run build` / tests are fine when useful to verify work.
- When the user asks to deploy, use the existing path: `/share/Container/FilmentsManagement/` and the project’s frontend/backend layout.

## Git (off by default)

- Do not `git commit`, `git push`, or open PRs unless the user explicitly asks.
- Showing `git status` / diff to explain changes is fine; staging and committing require explicit request.
- Follow the user’s git safety rules when they do ask for commits or pushes.

## After completing work

- Summarize what changed locally and remind the user they can ask to deploy or push when ready — do not do either automatically.
